HEADWORD: jury-rigged
<hw>ju"ry-rigged`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<def>Rigged for temporary service; done or made using whatever materials
are available; makeshift; <as>as, the survivors used
<ex>jury-rigged</ex> fishing gear</as>. See <er>Jury</er>,
<pos>a.</pos></def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> improvised, makeshift.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

